  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO CREATE THE MISSISSIPPI YOUTH AND FAMILY SYSTEMS COORDINATION TASK FORCE, WHICH IS A STATEWIDE, MULTISYSTEM BODY WHOSE PURPOSE IS TO DEVELOP AND COORDINATE RESEARCH-BASED STRATEGIES CONSISTENT WITH THE YOUTH COURT LAW AND THE STATE'S BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SYSTEM; TO PROVIDE THE MEMBERSHIP AND DUTIES OF THE TASK FORCE; TO REQUIRE THE TASK FORCE TO SUBMIT AN ANNUAL REPORT TO THE GOVERNOR AND THE LEGISLATURE; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
  },
